<Table
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    CellSpacing="4"
    Background="Wheat">

    <Table.Resources>
        <Style x:Key="cellBody" TargetType="{x:Type TableCell}">
            <Setter Property="BorderThickness" Value="1,1,1,1" />
            <Setter Property="BorderBrush" Value="Black" />
            <Setter Property="Padding" Value="4" />
            <Setter Property="Background" Value="White" />
            <Setter Property="Foreground" Value="Black" />
            <Setter Property="FontSize" Value="9pt" />
        </Style>
    </Table.Resources>

    <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
            <TableCell Style="{DynamicResource cellBody}">\
<Paragraph>
The bandage was wound around the wound. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
The farm was used to produce produce. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
The dump was so full that it had to refuse more refuse. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
We must polish the Polish furniture. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
He could lead if he would get the lead out. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
The soldier decided to desert his dessert in the desert. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
Since there is no time like the present, he thought it was time to present the present. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
A bass was painted on the head of the bass drum. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
When shot at, the dove dove into the bushes. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
I did not object to the object. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
The insurance was invalid for the invalid. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
There was a row among the oarsmen about how to row. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
They were too close to the door to close it. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
The buck does funny things when the does are present. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
A seamstress and a sewer fell down into a sewer line. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
To help with planting, the farmer taught his sow to sow. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
The wind was too strong to wind the sail. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
After a number of injections my jaw got number. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
Upon seeing the tear in the painting I shed a tear. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
I had to subject the subject to a series of tests. <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
How can I intimate this to my most intimate friend? <LineBreak /><LineBreak />
I want it to be on record that I will record my record.
</Paragraph>
            </TableCell>
        </TableRow>
    </TableRowGroup>
</Table>

